text: A lot of the Cuba news got buried this week, but it reminds me of this cool story about how Cubans stay hip despite limited-to-no Internet access: <https://torrentfreak.com/el-paquete-semanal-how-offline-piracy-flourishes-in-cuba-151226/>

attachments.title: El Paquete Semanal: How Offline Piracy Flourishes in Cuba - TorrentFreak
attachments.text: For more than a decade many Cubans have been pirating the latest entertainment without a proper connection to the Internet. Instead, they have built their own person-to-person distribution network to share a weekly package of pirated material: El Paquete Semanal.
